hit R_com: DgHowkFt8HW7LZYb2gzehzxHamxuAZ . Summary The v2 artifact does not appear to be recoverable from the public files alone. The single published break (v1, a different wallet) used an R_com commitment that acted as an offline guess checker. v2 removes that commitment from the wire and wraps every block with two independent masks, which removes the ability to verify a plaintext guess at all. This page documents the scheme, the one public value that depends on the plaintext, and every attack path checked so far, including the LPN direction.
