hit second ciphertext: nce, which retired the information theoretic hiding claim, but it did not add anything that lifts the mask, so the practical result held. What would actually change it is either a second ciphertext under the same key, which would break the one time pad property, or an exposure of sk.prf_k , the 256 bit secret that gates every mask. A published prf_k , or samples for the r2 and r3 domains plus a feasible way to solve them, would be the real unlock. Absent that, there is no path from these public files to the plaintext. Reproduce g++ -s
